es","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Henry Hoghton was born about 1428, in Arundel, Sussex, England as the son of Richard de Hoghton. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1428–":"umbes 1428–Surnud","1421–1479":"1421–1479","1428–Male":"1428–Surnud","1449–1491":"1449–1491","1399–1468":"1399–1468","about 1428":"umbes 1428","1468":"1468","1479":"1479","1455":"1455","1399":"1399","1421":"1421","1491":"1491","1428":"1428","1449":"1449","of Arundel, Sussex, England":"Arundel, Sussex, England"},"fi":{"about 1428–":"noin 1428–Kuollut","1421–1479":"1421–1479","1428–Male":"1428–Kuollut","1449–1491":"1449–1491","1399–1468":"1399–1468","about 1428":"noin 1428","1468":"1468","1479":"1479","1455":"1455","1399":"1399","1421":"1421","1491":"1491","1428":"1428","1449":"1449","of Arundel, Sussex, England":"Arundel, Sussex, England"},"fr":{"about 1428–":"environ 1428–Décédé","1421–1479":"1421–1479","1428–Male":"1428–Décédé","1449–1491":"1449–1491","1399–1468":"1399–1468","about 1428":"environ 1428","1468":"1468","1479":"1479","1455":"1455","1399":"1399","1421":"1421","1491":"1491","1428":"1428","1449":"1449","of Arundel, Sussex, England":"Arundel, Sussex, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Henry Hoghton est né environ 1428, à Arundel, Sussex, Angleterre, fils de Richard de Hoghton. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"about 1428–":"um 1428–Verstorben","1421–1479":"1421–1479","1428–Male":"1428–Verstorben","1449–1491":"1449–1491","1399–1468":"1399–1468","about 1428":"um 1428","1468":"1468","1479":"1479","1455":"1455","1399":"1399","1421":"1421","1491":"1491","1428":"1428","